"title": "5093: Eve",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5093",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The wife of Adam and the first woman created. Her significance lies in being the first to be deceived and become disobedient to God. She is only given her name (which resembles the word for “living”) by Adam after the expulsion from Eden.</p>\n<h2>Eve was created in the image of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:27\">GEN 1:27</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Eve was a companion for Adam in Eden</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:18\">GEN 2:18</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Eve was deceived</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:1-Gen3:7\">GEN 3:1–3:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:13\">GEN 3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:3\">2CO 11:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:13-1Tim2:14\">1TI 2:13–2:14</a></p>\n<h2>Events in Eve's life</h2>\n<h3>Her creation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:26-Gen1:27\">GEN 1:26–1:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:21-Gen2:23\">GEN 2:21–2:23</a></p>\n<h3>Her shame</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:8-Gen3:13\">GEN 3:8–3:13</a></p>\n<h3>The curse upon her</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:16\">GEN 3:16</a></p>\n<h3>Adam names her</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:20\">GEN 3:20</a></p>\n<h3>The LORD clothes her</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:21\">GEN 3:21</a></p>\n<h3>She becomes a mother</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:1-Gen4:2\">GEN 4:1–4:2</a></p>",
